obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (44265)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Married Womens Property Act, 1874.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44265&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (44256)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Extent an application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44256&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir*.]
  line
  line `But nothing herein contained applies to any married woman who at the time of her marriage`
  line `professed the Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jain a religion, or whose husband, at the time`
  line `of such marriage, professed any of those religions.`
  line
  line `And the ^2[State Government] may from time to time, by order, either retrospectively from the`
  line `passing of this Act or prospectively, exempt from the operation of all or any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act the members of any race, sect or tribe or part of a race, sect or tribe, to whom it may consider it`
  line `impossible or inexpedient to apply such provisions.`
  line
  line `The ^2[State Government] may also revoke any such order, but not so that the revocation shall have`
  line `any retrospective effect.`
  line
  line `All orders and revocations under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line ^3
  line *****
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 61 of 1959, s. 2, for the former para. (w.e.f. 1-3-1960).`
  line
  line `2. The original words "G.G. in C." have successively been amended by Act 38 of 1920, the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950 to`
  line `read as above.`
  line
  line `3. The last paragraph rep. by Act 39 of 1925, s. 392 and the Ninth Schedule. .`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44257)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Repealed..
  content `[Commencement.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1876 (12 of 1876), s. 1 and Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44257&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (44266)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Married women’s earnings to be their separate property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44266&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^14. Married womens earnings to be their separate property.The wages and earnings of any`
  line `married woman acquired or gained by her after the passing of this Act, in any employment,`
  line `occupation or trade carried on by her and not by her husband,`
  line
  line `and also any money or other property so acquired by her through the exercise of any literary,`
  line `artistic or scientific skill,`
  line
  line `and all savings from and investments of such wages, earnings and property,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be her separate property, and her receipts alone shall be good discharges for`
  line `such wages, earnings and property.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cf. the Married Women's Property Act 1870 (33 and 34 Vict., c. 93), s. 1, now rep. by Married Women's Property Act,`
  line `1882 (45 and 46 Vict., c. 75).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (44267)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Married woman may effect policy of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Cf. the Married Women's Property Act, 1870 (33 and 34 Vict., c. 93), s. 10, para. 1.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44267&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1Any married woman may effect a policy`
  line `of insurance on her own behalf and independently of her husband; and the same and all benefit,`
  line `thereof, if expressed on the face of it to be so effected, shall enure as her separate property, and the`
  line `contract evidenced by such policy shall be as valid as if made with an unmarried woman.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (44260)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Insurance by husband for benefit of wife.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44260&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^16. Insurance by husband for benefit of wife.`
  line `^2[(1) A policy of insurance effected by any`
  line `married man on his own life, and expressed on the face of it to be for the benefit of his wife, or of his`
  line `wife and children, or any of them, shall ensure and be deemed to be a trust for the benefit of his wife,`
  line `or of his wife and children, or any of them, according to the interest so expressed, and shall not, so`
  line `long any object of the trust remains, be subject to the control of the husbands or to his creditors, or`
  line `form part of his estate.`
  line
  line `When the sum secured by the policy becomes payable, it shall, unless special trustees are duly`
  line `appointed to receive and hold the same, be paid to the Official Trustee of the ^3[State] in which the`
  line `office at which the insurance was effected is situated, and shall be received and held by him upon the`
  line `trusts expressed in the policy, or such of them as are then existing.`
  line
  line `And in reference to such sum he shall stand in the same position in all respects as if he had been`
  line `duly appointed trustee thereof by a High Court, under Act No. 17 of 1864 ^4`
  line `[to constitute an Office of`
  line `Official Trustee], Section 10.`
  line
  line `Nothing herein contained shall operate to destroy or impede the right of any creditor to be paid out`
  line `of the proceeds of any policy of assurance which may have been effected with intent to defraud`
  line creditors.
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 2, the provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply`
  line `in the case of any policy of insurance such as is referred to therein which effected--`
  line
  line `(a) by any Hindu, Muhammedan, Sikh or Jain--`
  line
  line `(i) in Madras, after the thirty-first day of December, 1913, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other territory to which this Act extended immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the Married Women's Property (Extension) Act, 1959 (61 of 1959), after the first day of`
  line `April, 1923, or`
  line
  line `(iii) in any territory to which this Act extends on and from the commencement of the Married`
  line `Women's Property (Extension) Act, 1959 (61 of 1959),`
  line
  line `(b) by a Buddhist in any territory to which this Act extends, on or after the commencement of the`
  line `Married Women's Property (Extension) Act, 1959 (61 of 1959):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall affect any right or liability which has accrued or been`
  line `incurred under any decree of a competent Court passed--`
  line
  line `(i) before the first day of April, 1923, in any case to which sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `Clause (a) applies ; or`
  line
  line `(ii) before the commencement of the Married Women's Property (Extension) Act, 1959, in any`
  line `case to which sub-clause (iii) of Clause (a) or Clause (b) applies.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cf. the Married Women's Property Act, 1870 (33 and 34 Vict., c. 93), s.10, para. 2.`
  line
  line `2. S. 6 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 13 of 1923, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. The word "Presidency" has been successively amended by the A.O. 1937, the A.O. 1950 and the Adaptation of Laws`
  line `(No. 2) Order, 1956, to read as above.`
  line
  line `4. The relevant provisions of the Official Trustees Act, 1913 (2 of 1913) may be referred to.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 61 of 1959, s. 3 for sub-section (2), (w.e.f. 1-3-1960), Earlier inserted by 13 of 1923, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (44268)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Married woman may take legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44268&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^17. Married women may take legal proceedings.A married woman may maintain a suit in her`
  line `own name for the recovery of property of any description which, by force of the said Indian`
  line `Succession Act, 1865^2`
  line `(10 of 1865) or of this Act, is her separate property; and she shall have, in her`
  line `own name, the same remedies, both civil and criminal, against all persons, for the protection and`
  line `security of such property, as is she were unmarried, and she shall be liable to such suits, processes`
  line `and orders in respect of such property as she would be liable to if she were unmarried.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cf. the Married Women's Property Act, 1870 (33 and 34 Vict., c.93), s. 11, rep. By the Married Women's Property Act,`
  line `1882 (45 and 46 Vict., c.75).`
  line
  line `2. See now the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (44262)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Wifes liability for postnuptial debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1929, s. 2, for the proviso.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44262&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If a married woman (whether married before or after`
  line `the first day of January, 1866) possesses separate property, and if any person enters into a contract`
  line `with her with reference to such property, or on the faith that her obligation arising out of such contract`
  line `will be satisfied out of her separate property, such person shall be entitled to sue her, and to the extent`
  line `of her separate property, to recover against her whatever he might have recovered in such suit had she`
  line `been unmarried at the date of the contract and continued unmarried at the execution of the decree :`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that nothing herein contained shall--`
  line
  line `(a) entitle such person to recover anything by attachment and sale or otherwise out of any`
  line `property which has been transferred to a woman or for her benefit on condition that she shall have`
  line `no power during her marriage to transfer or charge the same or her beneficial interest therein, or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the liability of a husband for debts contracted by his wifes agency expressed or`
  line implied.]
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (44269)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Husband not liable for wife’s antenuptial debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44269&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^19. Husband not liable for wifes ante-nuptial debts.A husband married after the thirty-first`
  line `day of December, 1865 shall not by reason only of such marriage be liable to the debts of hi s wife`
  line `contracted before marriage, but the wife shall be liable to be sued for, and shall, to the extent of her`
  line `separate property, be liable to satisfy such debts as if he had continued unmarried:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall ^2`
  line `*** invalidate any contract into which a`
  line `husband may, before the passing of this Act, have entered in consideration of hi s wife's ante-nuptial`
  line debts.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cf. the Married Woman's Property Act, 1870 (33 and 34 Viet., c. 93), s. 12.`
  line
  line `2. The words "affect any suit instituted before the passing of this Act, not" rep. By Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (44270)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Extent of husband’s liability for wife’s breach of trust or devastation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1927, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897&sectionId=44270&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00037_187403_1523269675897
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1, Where a woman is`
  line `a trustee, executrix or administratrix, either before or after marriage, her husband shall not, unless he`
  line `acts or intermeddles in the trust or administration, be liable for any breach of trust committed by her,`
  line `or for any misapplication, loss or damage to the estate of the deceased caused or made by her, or for`
  line `any loss to such estate arising from her neglect to get in any part of the property of deceased.`
